        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:07PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Waynesville, or near B.R. Parkway-Smoky Mountains To
Balsam Gap, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Waynesville, Sylva, Lake Junaluska, Clyde, Maggie Valley, Balsam,
B.R. Parkway-Smoky Mountains To Balsam Gap, B.R. Parkway-Balsam Gap
To Black Balsam Area, Cherokee, and Cove Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
